did.abstract: This collection contains the records of the University Librarian for George Washington University. Materials in this collection include budgets, reports, and working files. They range in date from 1991 to 2008, with the bulk of the material dating between 1994 and 1995.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Materials were transferred to the University Archives by the University Librarian.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The George Washington University's Melvin Gelman Library opened in 1973. Before the Gelman Library (which received its current name in 1980), the University Library was located in Lisner Hall, formerly Lisner Library. When the University moved to Foggy Bottom in 1912 from its location on 15th and H Streets, N.W., the first library was located in the original Lisner Hall, the former St. Rose's School for Orphaned Girls, between 20th and 21st Streets on G Street. Other libraries include the Virginia Campus Library (established n 1990), and the Mount Vernon Campus Eckles Library (under GW control since 1997). Together, these three libraries form the Gelman Library System (GLS).

The Library is headed by a University Librarian, who oversees: the Assistant University Librarian, Administration, Development, and Personnel; Associate University Librarian for Collections and Scholarly Communication; Associate University Librarian for Information Technology; Associate University Librarian for Public Services; Directors of the Mt. Vernon and Virginia Campus libraries, and the Manager of GLS (Gelman Library System) Financial Operations.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection include budgets, reports, and working files from the office of the University Librarian. They range in date from 1991 to 2008.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into two series: Office files and Jack Siggins records [accession 2012.071]

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Series 1 is open for research. Series 2 is closed for 50 years from date of record creation.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains office files related to the subjects of the staff management group (smg), budget, WRLC, GW Tidewater and Hampton locations, computer information center, university policies, Virginia Campus Library, faculty senate, friends of the libraries group. The records cover the years 1992-96.
